<item>
            <title>[SUREFIRE-920] -Dmaven.test.failure.ignore=true isn&apos;t honored</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-920</link>
                <project id="12317927" key="SUREFIRE">Maven Surefire (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I have a multi module project and running the build in jenkins with -Dmaven.test.failure.ignore=true&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When one of the module has a failed test, the build fails right at that point instead of ignoring the failure and moving on to run tests in the next module.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I took a look at SurefirePlugin.handleSummary() method it&apos;s not checking for isTestFailureIgnore() value. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
